docs/combat_mixed_pattern_drift_ledger.md:13:- Preserve the canonical decisions already established in memory: typed hook/kernel seams stay canonical, presentation beats are non-authoritative, and shared combat systems should remain branch-light.
docs/combat_mixed_pattern_drift_ledger.md:22:| D4 | High | `src/combat/follow_up.rs`, `src/data/units_ron.rs` | rewrite-scale/follow-up candidate | S03 | Seed a per-Digimon blueprint seam in Rust, but keep the shared combat systems branch-light and do not complete a full migration inside S02. |
docs/combat_mixed_pattern_drift_ledger.md:23:| D5 | Medium | `src/data/skills_ron.rs`, `tests/holy_support_roster_contract.rs` | obsolete/stale test drift | S03 | Treat RON custom-signal expectations as stale-test coupling unless S03 explicitly chooses a new contract; do not reintroduce removed `Effect` variants just to satisfy old assumptions. |
docs/combat_mixed_pattern_drift_ledger.md:26:| D8 | Medium | `src/data/skills_ron.rs`, `src/combat/resolution.rs` | safe placeholder | S04 | Add an explicit contract proof that `animation_sequence` and `qte` remain presentation metadata and do not alter combat resolution. |
docs/combat_mixed_pattern_drift_ledger.md:37:The rewrite-scale work is the per-Digimon blueprint migration. The codebase does **not** already have a full blueprint ownership layer, so D4 is not something to “finish” inside S02. S03 should seed the seam in a small typed slice, then let later work expand it without forcing the whole combat model to move at once.
docs/combat_mixed_pattern_drift_ledger.md:48:**Code seam to inspect:** the boundary between shared combat systems and presentation-adjacent metadata.
docs/combat_mixed_pattern_drift_ledger.md:50:**Handoff note:** R094 is about avoiding false authority claims. S04 should prove that presentation metadata stays non-authoritative and that any future blueprint seam does not leak into shared resolution code.
docs/combat_mixed_pattern_drift_ledger.md:72:**Code seam to inspect:** beat vocabulary, presentation metadata, and the action-resolution pipeline.
docs/combat_mixed_pattern_drift_ledger.md:74:**Handoff note:** R097 separates typed beat vocabulary from gameplay authority. If a later slice emits beats, that emission must still flow through the kernel/shared event seam rather than moving authority into presentation fields.
docs/combat_mixed_pattern_drift_ledger.md:93:Use this ledger as the owner map for normalization work. Fix the local wiring first, keep the shared combat systems branch-light, and treat blueprint migration as a seeded follow-up rather than an invisible rewrite hidden inside S02.
